docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The top two officials overseeing the military commissions court at the Guantánamo Bay wartime prison were fired last month because they were difficult to work with, not because of the officials’ legal actions, Secretary of Defense Jim Mattis and the Pentagon’s general counsel have told a judge.

headline.main: Mattis Says Guantánamo Lawyers Were Fired Over Temperament, Not Legal Work
